---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout title="FAQ — RADIANX CAPITAL" description="Frequently asked questions about RADIANX CAPITAL's wealth management services, fees, and investment process." currentPath="/faq">

<header class="faq-hero">
  <div class="faq-hero-inner">
    <div class="fh-tag">Common Questions</div>
    <h1 class="fh-h">Everything you need<br><em>to know.</em></h1>
    <p class="fh-desc">Transparent answers to the questions prospective and current clients ask most.</p>
  </div>
</header>

<section class="faq-section">
  <div class="faq-inner">

    <div class="faq-group rv">
      <div class="fg-label">About RADIANX</div>
      <div class="faq-items">
        <details class="faq-item">
          <summary>What is RADIANX CAPITAL?</summary>
          <div class="faq-ans">RADIANX CAPITAL, LLC is a New York-based SEC-registered investment adviser (CRD# 298178). We provide comprehensive wealth management services to high-net-worth individuals, families, and institutions — operating exclusively under the fiduciary standard since November 2017.</div>
        </details>
        <details class="faq-item">
          <summary>Are you a fiduciary?</summary>
          <div class="faq-ans">Yes — always. As an SEC-registered investment adviser, we are legally required to act in your best interest at all times. This is not a standard we optionally apply — it is a legal obligation that governs every recommendation, every decision, and every communication.</div>
        </details>
        <details class="faq-item">
          <summary>How are you regulated?</summary>
          <div class="faq-ans">RADIANX CAPITAL is registered with the U.S. Securities and Exchange Commission (SEC No. 801-117100, CRD# 298178, EIN: 82-3414149). You can verify our registration and review our Form ADV on the SEC's Investment Adviser Public Disclosure database at adviserinfo.sec.gov.</div>
        </details>
        <details class="faq-item">
          <summary>Where are you located?</summary>
          <div class="faq-ans">Our office is located at 529 5th Avenue, Suite 1475, New York, NY 10017. While we are headquartered in New York, we work with clients across the United States.</div>
        </details>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="faq-group rv d1">
      <div class="fg-label">Fees &amp; Costs</div>
      <div class="faq-items">
        <details class="faq-item">
          <summary>How do you charge for your services?</summary>
          <div class="faq-ans">We operate on a fee-only basis. Our fees are based on a percentage of assets under management (AUM), charged quarterly. We do not earn commissions, referral fees, or any form of compensation from third parties. All fees are fully disclosed in our Form ADV, which is available upon request.</div>
        </details>
        <details class="faq-item">
          <summary>Do you charge for financial planning separately?</summary>
          <div class="faq-ans">Comprehensive financial planning — including retirement, tax, estate, and cash flow planning — is integrated into our wealth management service for qualifying clients. There is no separate charge for planning when assets are managed with us above minimum thresholds.</div>
        </details>
        <details class="faq-item">
          <summary>What is your minimum investment?</summary>
          <div class="faq-ans">Our typical minimum for comprehensive wealth management is $1 million in investable assets. However, we evaluate each prospective client individually. We encourage you to contact us to discuss your specific situation before assuming you do or do not qualify.</div>
        </details>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="faq-group rv d2">
      <div class="fg-label">Investment Process</div>
      <div class="faq-items">
        <details class="faq-item">
          <summary>Do you use model portfolios?</summary>
          <div class="faq-ans">No. Every client portfolio is built from the ground up — tailored to your specific goals, tax situation, time horizon, income needs, and risk tolerance. We do not slot clients into pre-packaged model portfolios. Your portfolio reflects your life, not a template.</div>
        </details>
        <details class="faq-item">
          <summary>What asset classes do you invest in?</summary>
          <div class="faq-ans">We invest across a broad spectrum: domestic and international equities, fixed income, real assets, and alternatives including private equity, private credit, and hedge strategies (for qualified clients). Asset class selection is always driven by your specific objectives and time horizon.</div>
        </details>
        <details class="faq-item">
          <summary>How often will you communicate with me?</summary>
          <div class="faq-ans">You will receive formal portfolio reviews at least quarterly, with written performance reports and attribution analysis. Beyond scheduled reviews, we are accessible throughout the year — for market updates, life event planning, or simply questions. You will never feel like a number.</div>
        </details>
        <details class="faq-item">
          <summary>How do you handle tax management?</summary>
          <div class="faq-ans">Tax efficiency is embedded into every investment decision — not added as an afterthought. We implement continuous tax-loss harvesting, asset location optimization, Roth conversion analysis, and coordinate directly with your CPA or tax attorney throughout the year.</div>
        </details>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="faq-group rv">
      <div class="fg-label">Getting Started</div>
      <div class="faq-items">
        <details class="faq-item">
          <summary>How do I get started?</summary>
          <div class="faq-ans">The first step is a complimentary consultation — an unhurried conversation about your financial situation, goals, and what you're looking for in an adviser. There is no obligation, no pressure, and no sales pitch. Contact us at invest@radianx.io or call (646) 403-3807 to schedule.</div>
        </details>
        <details class="faq-item">
          <summary>What happens in the first meeting?</summary>
          <div class="faq-ans">We listen first. We will ask thorough questions about your current financial position, future goals, concerns, existing relationships, and what an ideal outcome looks like for you. At the end, we will tell you honestly whether and how we can add meaningful value — and what working together would look like.</div>
        </details>
        <details class="faq-item">
          <summary>How long does it take to onboard?</summary>
          <div class="faq-ans">From initial consultation to completed onboarding typically takes two to four weeks, depending on the complexity of your financial situation and account transfers. We manage the process thoroughly and communicate at every step to ensure a smooth transition.</div>
        </details>
      </div>
    </div>

  </div>
</section>

<section class="faq-cta">
  <div class="fcta-inner rv">
    <h2 class="fcta-h">Still have questions?<br><em>Let's talk.</em></h2>
    <p class="fcta-body">The best way to understand whether RADIANX is right for you is a direct conversation. We'll answer anything — honestly.</p>
    <div class="fcta-btns">
      <a href="/contact" class="btn-primary-dark">Schedule a Consultation</a>
      <a href="mailto:invest@radianx.io" class="btn-secondary-dark">Email Us Directly</a>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

</Layout>

<style is:global>
.faq-hero {
  background: #0b0b0d;
  padding: 160px 64px 100px;
  position: relative; overflow: hidden;
  border-bottom: 1px solid rgba(238,240,245,.06);
}
.faq-hero::before {
  content: ''; position: absolute;
  top: -10%; right: -5%; width: 50%; height: 80%;
  background: radial-gradient(ellipse at 70% 30%, rgba(122,150,168,.05) 0%, transparent 65%);
  pointer-events: none;
}
.faq-hero-inner { max-width: 720px; position: relative; z-index: 1; }
.fh-tag {
  font-family: 'DM Mono', monospace; font-size: 9px; letter-spacing: 4px;
  text-transform: uppercase; color: rgba(238,240,245,.35); margin-bottom: 24px;
  display: flex; align-items: center; gap: 12px;
}
.fh-tag::before { content: ''; width: 28px; height: 1px; background: #7a96a8; opacity: .6; }
.fh-h {
  font-family: 'Cormorant Garamond', serif;
  font-size: clamp(48px, 5.5vw, 82px); font-weight: 300;
  line-height: .95; letter-spacing: -2px; color: #f0eeeb; margin-bottom: 28px;
}
.fh-h em { font-style: italic; color: rgba(240,238,235,.6); }
.fh-desc {
  font-family: 'Outfit', sans-serif; font-size: 16px; font-weight: 300;
  color: rgba(238,240,245,.45); line-height: 1.8;
}

/* FAQ body */
.faq-section { background: #fafaf8; padding: 80px 64px; border-bottom: 1px solid rgba(13,17,23,.08); }
.faq-inner { max-width: 860px; margin: 0 auto; display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 56px; }

.faq-group {}
.fg-label {
  font-family: 'DM Mono', monospace; font-size: 9px; letter-spacing: 3.5px;
  text-transform: uppercase; color: #1a2e52; opacity: .6;
  margin-bottom: 20px; padding-bottom: 14px;
  border-bottom: 1px solid rgba(13,17,23,.08);
}
.faq-items { display: flex; flex-direction: column; }
.faq-item {
  border-bottom: 1px solid rgba(13,17,23,.06);
}
.faq-item summary {
  font-family: 'Outfit', sans-serif; font-size: 16px; font-weight: 400;
  color: #0d1117; padding: 20px 0; cursor: pointer;
  list-style: none; display: flex; justify-content: space-between; align-items: center;
  transition: color .2s;
}
.faq-item summary::-webkit-details-marker { display: none; }
.faq-item summary::after {
  content: '+'; font-family: 'DM Mono', monospace; font-size: 18px;
  color: rgba(13,17,23,.3); transition: transform .3s, color .2s;
  flex-shrink: 0; margin-left: 24px;
}
.faq-item[open] summary { color: #1a2e52; }
.faq-item[open] summary::after { transform: rotate(45deg); color: #1a2e52; }
.faq-ans {
  font-family: 'Outfit', sans-serif; font-size: 14.5px; font-weight: 300;
  color: rgba(13,17,23,.6); line-height: 1.85;
  padding: 0 0 24px 0; max-width: 680px;
}

/* CTA */
.faq-cta { background: #0e1220; padding: 96px 64px; }
.fcta-inner { max-width: 580px; margin: 0 auto; text-align: center; }
.fcta-h {
  font-family: 'Cormorant Garamond', serif;
  font-size: clamp(36px, 4vw, 54px); font-weight: 300; line-height: 1.1;
  color: #f0eeeb; margin-bottom: 18px;
}
.fcta-h em { font-style: italic; color: rgba(240,238,235,.55); }
.fcta-body {
  font-family: 'Outfit', sans-serif; font-size: 15px; font-weight: 300;
  color: rgba(238,240,245,.4); line-height: 1.8; margin-bottom: 36px;
}
.fcta-btns { display: flex; gap: 12px; justify-content: center; flex-wrap: wrap; }
.btn-primary-dark {
  font-family: 'DM Mono', monospace; font-size: 10px; letter-spacing: 2px;
  text-transform: uppercase; color: #0e1220; background: #f0eeeb;
  border-radius: 2px; padding: 13px 28px; text-decoration: none; transition: background .25s;
}
.btn-primary-dark:hover { background: #fff; }
.btn-secondary-dark {
  font-family: 'DM Mono', monospace; font-size: 10px; letter-spacing: 2px;
  text-transform: uppercase; color: rgba(240,238,235,.55);
  border: 1px solid rgba(240,238,235,.18); border-radius: 2px; padding: 13px 28px;
  text-decoration: none; transition: all .25s;
}
.btn-secondary-dark:hover { border-color: rgba(240,238,235,.4); color: #f0eeeb; }

@media (max-width: 768px) {
  .faq-hero { padding: 130px 24px 72px; }
  .faq-section { padding: 56px 24px; }
  .faq-cta { padding: 72px 24px; }
}
@media (max-width: 480px) {
  .faq-hero { padding: 110px 20px 60px; }
  .faq-section { padding: 40px 20px; }
}

.rv { opacity: 0; transform: translateY(18px); transition: opacity .7s ease, transform .7s ease; }
.rv.in { opacity: 1; transform: none; }
.rv.d1 { transition-delay: .1s; }
.rv.d2 { transition-delay: .2s; }
</style>

<script is:inline>
const io = new IntersectionObserver(e => e.forEach(x => {
  if (x.isIntersecting) { x.target.classList.add('in'); io.unobserve(x.target); }
}), { threshold: .08 });
document.querySelectorAll('.rv').forEach(el => io.observe(el));
</script>

